  "body": "Sometimes, why the current block height is 1 when the 'geth' reboot ( height is 100 before), so it tooltips `ErrKnownBlock = errors.New(\"block already known\")`\r\nIf the geth reboot, why the block height is 1 or less than 100 (which before reboot)?\r\n```\r\n// ValidateBody validates the given block's uncles and verifies the block\r\n// header's transaction and uncle roots. The headers are assumed to be already\r\n// validated at this point.\r\nfunc (v *BlockValidator) ValidateBody(block *types.Block) error {\r\n\t// Check whether the block's known, and if not, that it's linkable\r\n\tif v.bc.HasBlockAndState(block.Hash(), block.NumberU64()) {\r\n\t\treturn ErrKnownBlock\r\n\t}\r\n.....\r\n```",
